Program: Discovery
Title: HIV and Aids in Africa
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrxy4
Last Broadcast Date: 31 October 2001
The massive problem of HIV infection in Africa. There are 9 African countries which have had a reduction of 20 years or more in their average life expectancies. The social and economic effects of the HIV epidemic are likely to be huge, and an affordable and effective vaccine cannot come soon enough.